National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: MIAMI, FL
Accident Number: MIA82DA103
Date & Time: 04/01/1982, 0730 EST
Registration: N3587D
Aircraft: PIPER PA-31-350
Aircraft Damage: Substantial
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 91: General Aviation -
 Analysis THE PILOT WAS TAXIING TO GATE H-2 TO PICK UP A CHARTER PASSENGER WHEN THE AIRCRAFT AND A VEHICLE COLLIDED.
THE PILOT REPORTED THAT ABOUT FIVE SECONDS BEFORE IMPACT, HE SAW THE VEHICLE APPROACHING FROM HIS TEN O'CLOCK POSITION.
HE APPLIED THE BRAKES, BUT THE VEHICLE CROSSED IN FRONT OF THE AIRCRAFT AND STRUCK THE RIGHT WINGTIP.
THE DRIVER OF THE VEHICLE WAS ESCORTING ANOTHER VEHICLE.
HE STATED THAT HE LOOKED BOTH WAYS BEFORE ENTERING THE TAXIWAY, BUT DID NOT SEE ANY MOVING AIRCRAFT.
WHEN HE NOTICED THE PLANE, HE ACCELERATED TO AVOID COLLISION, BUT WAS TOO LATE.
IT WAS NOTED THAT THERE WAS A BRIGHT MORNING SUN REFLECTING ON A WET PAVEMENT THAT MAY HAVE HINDERED THE DRIVER'S VISION.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: ON GROUND/WATER COLLISION WITH OBJECT Phase of Operation: TAXI Findings 1.
(F) TERRAIN CONDITION - WET 2.
(F) LIGHT CONDITION - SUNGLARE 3.
(C) VISUAL LOOKOUT - INADEQUATE - PILOT IN COMMAND 4.
(F) OBJECT - VEHICLE 5.
